s the punch When vague desire is the fire in the eyes of chicks Whose sickness is the games - - they play - - And when the then masquerade is played an neibhours folks Make jokes as who is most to blame long comes Mary (Mary, Mary) And a- long comes Mary wanna set them free And let them see reality from where she got her name And will she struggle much when told that such a tender touch of hers will make them not the same met I was sure out to lunch - - now my empty cup tastes as sweet as the punch, sweet as the punch And when the morning of the warning''s passed The gassed and flaccid kids are flung a- cross - - the stars - - the psycho- dramas and the traumas gone the songs are left unsung and hung up- long comes Mary (Mary, Mary) And then a- wanna see the stains the dead re- mains of all the all the pains she left the night before? - - Or will the wakin‘ eyes reflect the lies and make them realize their urgent cry for met I was sure out to lunch - - now my empty", "_lrclib_synced": "[00:12.76] Every time I think that I''m\n[00:14.19] The only one who''s lonely someone calls on me\n[00:18.84] And every now and then I spend\n[00:20.17] My time at rhyme and verse and curse those faults in me\n[00:24.55] And then along comes Mary\n[00:26.60] Mary, Mary\n[00:27.73] Then along comes Mary\n[00:29.76] Mary, Mary\n[00:30.68] And does she wanna give me kicks\n[00:32.35] And be my steady chick and give me pick of memories?\n[00:36.97] Or maybe rather gather tales from all the\n[00:39.11] Fails and tribulations no one ever sees?\n[00:43.17] When we met I was sure out to lunch\n[00:45.83] Now my empty cup tastes as sweet as the punch\n[00:48.90] Sweet as the punch\n[00:50.48] \n[01:01.68] When vague desire is the fire in the eyes of chicks\n[01:04.45] Whose sickness is the games they play\n[01:07.92] And when the masquerade is played and neighbor folks\n[01:10.30] Make jokes as who is most to blame today\n[01:13.96] And then along comes Mary\n[01:16.11] Mary, Mary\n[01:17.37] Then along comes Mary\n[01:19.11] Mary, Mary\n[01:20.36] And does she wanna set them free\n[01:21.88] And let them see reality from where she got her name?\n[01:26.39] And will they struggle much when told that such\n[01:28.38] A tender touch of hers will make them not the same?\n[01:32.71] When we met I was sure out to lunch\n[01:35.44] Now my empty cup tastes as sweet as the punch\n[01:38.42] Sweet as the punch\n[01:39.99] \n[01:51.21] And when the morning of the warning''s passed\n[01:53.28] The gassed and flaccid kids are flung across the stars\n[01:57.40] The psychodramas and the traumas gone\n[01:59.35] The songs are left unsung and hung upon the scars\n[02:03.66] And then along comes Mary\n[02:05.86] Mary, Mary\n[02:06.76] Then along comes Mary\n[02:08.88] Mary, Mary\n[02:09.93] And does she wanna see the stains the dead remains\n[02:12.02] Of all the pains she left the night before?\n[02:15.63] Or will their wakin'' eyes reflect the lies\n[02:17.68] And make them realize their urgent cry for sight no more?\n[02:22.24] When we met I was sure out to lunch\n[02:24.91] Now my empty cup tastes as sweet as the punch\n[02:27.93] Sweet as the punch\n[02:29.49] \n[02:40.93] When we met I was sure out to lunch\n[02:43.59] Now my empty cup tastes as sweet as the punch\n[02:47.28] When we met I was sure out to lunch\n[02:49.95] Now my empty cup tastes as sweet as the punch\n[02:53.29] When we met I was sure out to lunch\n[02:56.14] Now my empty cup tastes as sweet as the punch\n[02:59.57] When we met I was sure out to lunch\n[03:02.26] Now my empty cup tastes as sweet as the punch\n[03:05.76] When we met I was sure out to lunch\n[03:08.53] Now my empty cup tastes as sweet as the punch\n[03:11.75] When we met I was sure out to lunch\n[03:14.74] Now my empty cup tastes as sweet as the punch\n[03:17.60] Sweet as the punch\n[03:19.56] ", "tms": {"manual_done": ["accents_any", "in_setlist", "bar_markers", "templates_set", "parts_identified"], "user_tasks": [], "manual_undon